lass=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E\u0026amp;\u0026amp;\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E(\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003Ebody \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E==\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E refbody \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E||\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E refbody \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E==\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E null \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E||\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003ERaytrace\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E(\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003Evessel_pos\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E,\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E dir\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E,\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E refbody\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E));\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E}\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n\n\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022com\u0022\u003E// example usage\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022kwd\u0022\u003Eif\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E(\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003ERaytraceBody\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E(\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003Evessel\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E,\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003EFlightGlobals\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E.\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003EBodies\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E[\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022lit\u0022\u003E0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E]))\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E{\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n  \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022com\u0022\u003E// sun is visible, turn off all the lights\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E}\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022kwd\u0022\u003Eelse\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E{\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n  \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022com\u0022\u003E// sun is occluded, turn on all the lights\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E}\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCheers for that, I have a semi working implementation now \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0unfortunately I can\u0027t test until tomorrow night, the source is available at\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/genericeventhandler/AutomaticLights\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/genericeventhandler/AutomaticLights\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0if anyone feels brave enough to compile it and try it out.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGE.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"fourfa","CreatedById":151713,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-28T16:19:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222690580\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022144484\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469467619\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110959\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Alshain\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn July 25, 2016 at 10:26 AM, Alshain said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlanetShine doesn\u0027t do that.\u00A0 PlanetShine renders reflected light from the daylight side of the planet (on the side of the craft facing the planet).\u00A0 It\u0027s a good mod but it doesn\u0027t generate light on the dark side of the planet.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTheoretically yes, but if you abuse the sliders it\u0027s simply light everywhere, always. KSP streamers using PlanetShine seem to do that a lot. And I sort of get it - it\u0027s one thing to play while fumbling around in pitch black, but something else to watch someone else do it\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit - er, maybe I\u0027m thinking of Scatterer? If only we could delete posts\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-07-28T16:20:37Z\u0022 title=\u002207/28/2016 04:20  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 28, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by fourfa\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alshain","CreatedById":110959,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-28T16:25:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222694742\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022144484\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469722751\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022151713\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022fourfa\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, fourfa said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTheoretically yes, but if you abuse the sliders it\u0027s simply light everywhere, always. KSP streamers using PlanetShine seem to do that a lot. And I sort of get it - it\u0027s one thing to play while fumbling around in pitch black, but something else to watch someone else do it\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit - er, maybe I\u0027m thinking of Scatterer? If only we could delete posts\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSP Streamers use this, it was made for that purpose:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/64901-113-ambient-light-adjustment-2585-220616-continued/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"genericeventhandler","CreatedById":149557,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-01T15:02:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi,\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve compiled a version and have been testing it all weekend, \u00A0 \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/genericeventhandler/AutomaticLights/archive/master.zip\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/genericeventhandler/AutomaticLights/archive/master.zip\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0 \u00A0find the gamedata folder in there and extract it as usual. - compiled against 1.1.2 - but should be compatible with 1.1.3.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAdd one of the copied lights to your crat, right click it and turn it on with the new button, if the EC is above 25% they will turn on when obscured from the sun, thanks ShotgunNinja,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTested on the ground, underwater, behind kerbin and some extensive off roading on The Mun.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGE\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"genericeventhandler","CreatedById":149557,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-19T17:56:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf anyone is interested, I\u0027ve updated the code to 1.2.2\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/genericeventhandler/AutomaticLights\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/genericeventhandler/AutomaticLights\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe lights now work correctly, and I\u0027ve add an autominer and autogenerator modules as we..\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nAutoLights turn off and on when hidden from the sun, checks to see if there is enough ElectricalCharge left.\u00A0\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nAutoGenerator - turns the generator off if EC \u0026lt;50% \u00A0turns on if resource \u0026lt; 99%\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nAutoMiner - Bit buggy, but will turn resource harvesters on and off if the watched resource is low. \u00A0Add to an ore drill and watch ore. It will mine until full then stop, or EC is low.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nIn the Electrical folder remove the autogenerator and autominer if not required.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGE\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Enceos","CreatedById":110725,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-19T19:06:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/149557-genericeventhandler/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022149557\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/149557-genericeventhandler/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@genericeventhandler\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0You didn\u0027t like the Crew Light mod?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/154901-122-crew-light-an-automatic-light-manager-14-17-feb-2017/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-02-19T19:07:07Z\u0022 title=\u002202/19/2017 07:07  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 19, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Enceos\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"genericeventhandler","CreatedById":149557,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-19T20:26:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222960850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022144484\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221487531177\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Enceos\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Enceos said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/149557-genericeventhandler/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022149557\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/149557-genericeventhandler/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@genericeventhandler\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0You didn\u0027t like the Crew Light mod?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt didn\u0027t exist when I wrote the first version. It works slightly differently though using a copy of the spot lights.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}